    <h1>Cookies Policy</h1>
    <p>This policy explains what cookies are, how we use them, and how they impact your browsing experience. Please take a moment to read this policy to understand the types of cookies we use, the information we collect through cookies, and how that information is used.</p>

    <p>Cookies are small files stored on your device that help us provide a better website experience. While cookies don’t typically contain information that can directly identify you, they may be linked to other personal data you’ve shared with us. For more details about how we handle your personal data securely, check out our <a href="#">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

    <p>We do not store sensitive information like passwords or mailing addresses in the cookies we use.</p>

    <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>
    <p>Cookies are small files placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit a website. They store details about your activity, such as browsing preferences or login details, to improve your experience.</p>

    <h2>Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
    <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Type:</strong> Session Cookies</li>
        <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> These cookies are critical for the website to function properly. They allow you to access services, log in securely, and protect against fraud. Without them, some features of the website may not work.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Functionality Cookies</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Type:</strong> Persistent Cookies</li>
        <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> These cookies help us remember your preferences, like your login details or language settings. They make your experience smoother by saving you from re-entering preferences every time you visit.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your Choices About Cookies</h2>
    <p>If you’d rather not use cookies, you can disable them in your browser settings. Once disabled, you can delete any cookies already stored. However, keep in mind that some website features may not work properly without cookies.</p>

